    "text": "Approximately 60% of the yield potential in foxtail millet breeding over 60 years is attributed to changes in varieties, and approximately 40% to improvements in cultivation measures. The genetic gains in grain yield were 35.79 kg ha-1 year-1 in 2023 and 29.29 kg ha-1 year-1 in 2024. The genetic gain in yield potential was 0.96% YOR-1.",
